 SLIDE 1 — Global Vision (AI for Production Urbanization)

Title

AI for Production Urbanization – A Unified Platform to Harmonize, Accelerate and Secure AI Initiatives

Impact Sentence

Creating a shared foundation for all AI projects, powered by the Digital Twin, the Knowledge Graph, Smart Engines, Agentic Platform, and the Doc-to-Knowledge capability.

Keywords

coherence, interoperability, shared capabilities, modernization, standardization, scalability

Highlight
	•	CTO alignment
	•	A transversal, enterprise-wide AI foundation
	•	Reduction of redundant work
	•	Faster AI delivery across all teams

⸻

⭐ SLIDE 2 — Why Urbanization? (The Problem)

Title

Why Do We Need AI Urbanization?

Impact Sentence

Today, each project develops its own models, pipelines, data logic, and agents — resulting in fragmentation, duplication, and inconsistent outcomes.

Keywords

silos, duplication, technical drift, inconsistent views, complexity, operational risks

Highlight
	•	Each team reinvents ingestion, analysis, rules, workflows
	•	No shared “truth” about the IT infrastructure
	•	AI efforts are scattered and hard to maintain
	•	Lack of interoperability between initiatives

⸻

⭐ PILLAR 1 — The Digital Twin (Common IT Source of Truth)

SLIDE 3 — The Digital Twin: A Unified Representation of IT

Impact Sentence

The Digital Twin is the backbone of Production AI, providing a consistent view of infrastructure, dependencies, events, metrics, and reliability paths.

Keywords

source of truth, dependencies, unified IT model, context, graph-based representation

Essential Bullets
	•	Models servers, pods, clusters, applications, networks
	•	Integrates incidents, changes, logs, metrics
	•	Captures runtime dependencies and impact paths
	•	Provides contextual intelligence to all AI projects

Highlight
	•	Foundation for correlation, risk scoring, RCA, automation
	•	Enables cross-team alignment
	•	Prevents every project from re-modeling the infrastructure

Value for other projects

Solvium, Changeum, LogListing → gain a shared, accurate view of infra & dependencies.

⸻

⭐ PILLAR 2 — Technical Architecture (From Ingestion to Agents)

SLIDE 4 — A Layered Architecture to Structure All AI Flows

Impact Sentence

A modular architecture that standardizes how data, knowledge, and intelligence flow through the ecosystem — from ingestion to execution.

Keywords

pipelines, STM, validation, knowledge graph, smart engines, agentic orchestration, exposure

Essential Bullets
	•	Ingestion Layer (Dynatrace, Elastic, SNOW, Network)
	•	Control & Quality Layer (validation, normalization, consistency)
	•	Knowledge Graph Layer (ontologies, dependencies, reasoning)
	•	Smart Engines Layer (ML, DL, GNN, neuro-symbolic)
	•	Agentic Layer (LangGraph orchestrations, agent behaviors)
	•	Exposure Layer (APIs, catalog, unified access)

Highlight
	•	A clear architecture map where every project knows where to plug in
	•	Ensures consistent processing across all initiatives

Value for other projects

Solvium, Changeum → reuse ingestion logic, consistency checks, graph reasoning.

⸻

⭐ PILLAR 3 — Exposed Services (APIs as Shared AI Capabilities)

SLIDE 5 — Smart Engines, Graph APIs, and Agentic Platform

Impact Sentence

We expose high-value AI services that any project can call: intelligence as APIs.

Keywords

AI-as-a-Service, Smart Engines, Graph APIs, Agentic PaaS, reusability, interoperability

Essential Bullets

1. Smart Engines-as-a-Service
	•	Incident Correlation Engine
	•	Integrity & Reliability Engine
	•	Anomaly Detection (GNN-ready)
	•	Change Risk Scoring
	•	Predictive Performance Engine

2. Knowledge Graph APIs
	•	Query entities & dependencies
	•	Service impact paths
	•	Historical event linking
	•	Graph reasoning functions
	•	Hybrid neuro-symbolic insights

3. Agentic Platform (LangGraph PaaS)
	•	Standardized agent execution
	•	Shared connectors (graph, engines, RAG)
	•	LLM/VLM access
	•	Versioned prompts & workflows
	•	Observability & governance

Highlight
	•	These shared services become the “AI backbone” for the entire Production ecosystem.

Value for other projects

Changeum → uses Change Risk Engine
Solvium → uses Integrity Engine, Graph APIs
LogListing → uses correlation & graph context
MIA → uses agents, graph, RAG

⸻

⭐ PILLAR 4 — Doc-to-Knowledge Platform (IDP)

SLIDE 6 — Turning Documents into Knowledge at Scale

Impact Sentence

A powerful ingestion and transformation pipeline to extract, structure, and integrate complex documents into the Knowledge Graph and the enterprise RAG.

Keywords

IDP, multimodal ingestion, OCR, VLM, document intelligence, LightRAG, GraphRAG

Essential Bullets
	•	Ingests complex formats (PDF, diagrams, images, tables)
	•	Uses OCR + VLM to extract structured signals
	•	Normalizes and maps content into graph ontology
	•	Feeds LightRAG / GraphRAG for retrieval
	•	Exposes knowledge to agents and Smart Engines

Highlight
	•	This turns unstructured knowledge into actionable, linked intelligence.

Value for other projects

Changeum → ingestion of CRQ, RFC, change records
Solvium → ingestion of lifecycle/obsolescence docs
MIA → doc-based assistance
LogListing → ingest large audit logs, error catalogs

⸻

⭐ PILLAR 5 — Agentic Platform Urbanization (Shared Agent Framework)

SLIDE 7 — A Common Framework for Building Cooperative Agents

Impact Sentence

We define a shared agentic ecosystem where teams can build agents that interoperate, collaborate, and compose complex workflows.

Keywords

LangGraph, multi-agent orchestration, personas, shared framework, reusability

Essential Bullets

Agent Personas
	•	Incident Manager
	•	Root Cause Analyst
	•	Change Mentor / Validator
	•	Application Expert
	•	Infrastructure Expert
	•	Obsolescence Advisor
	•	DocMaster
	•	Risk Mitigator

Framework Standardization
	•	Common prompts structure
	•	Shared access to graph, engines, RAG
	•	Governance for agent behaviors
	•	Standard state management (LangGraph)
	•	Versioning, tracing, auditability

Highlight
	•	Agents created by different teams can work together seamlessly.

Value for other projects

MIA → can consume shared personas
Changeum/Solvium → reuse RCA agent, Change Mentor
LogListing → use Log Analyst agent + graph context

⸻

⭐ PILLAR 6 — Governance & Collaboration Models

SLIDE 8 — Governance as the Glue of Urbanization

Impact Sentence

A clear governance framework ensures consistency, security, and long-term sustainability across all AI initiatives.

Keywords

standards, ontology, APIs contracts, security, lifecycle management, best practices

Essential Bullets
	•	AI Framework & Governance
	•	Ontology and graph standards
	•	API versioning & lifecycle
	•	LLM/VLM best practices
	•	Agent governance (roles, permissions, audit)
	•	Compliance, traceability, security-by-design
	•	Contribution model for external teams

Highlight
	•	Governance transforms a technical architecture into a shared enterprise AI ecosystem.

Value for other projects

Every team benefits from clarity, structure, and sustainable AI practices.

⸻

⭐ FINAL SLIDE — Summary & Value Proposition

Title

A Unified AI Platform to Empower Every Production Project

Impact Sentence

Urbanization provides a shared intelligence backbone so that all teams — Changeum, Solvium, LogListing, MIA, and others — can innovate faster using consistent, secure, and powerful AI capabilities.

Key Messages to Highlight
	•	Shared intelligence
	•	Shared knowledge
	•	Shared agents
	•	Shared APIs
	•	Shared graph
	•	Shared document pipeline

Outcome

Faster delivery, lower costs, higher quality, reduced operational risks, and stronger alignment with the CTO’s strategy.
